dcat-dataset-strings.title: Vicmap Elevation - Multi-Resolution Contours
dcat-dataset-strings.description:
SPATIAL DATAMART DELIVERY METHOD  -  'not available'.

Vicmap Elevation - Multi-Resolution Contours consists of project based  contours of varying intervals. The extent covers the major flood plains and Greater Melbourne. It does not include products available in Vicmap Elevation - Coastal 1m DEM & 0.5m Contours.

This data has been acquired between September 2007 and April 2012 through the Coordinated Imagery Program (CIP).

dcat-dataset-strings.title: Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m 2008
dcat-dataset-strings.description:
Obsolete, the Vicmap DTM 10M product has been significantly updated with new and revised content. and renamed to VICMAP_ELEV_DEM_10.

Vicmap Elevation DTM 10m is a product which is a raster representation of Victoria's elevation. DTM 10m has a spatial resolution of 10m. The DTM is constructed from source data of various resolutions, accuracies and ages to produce an improved DTM containing increased detail in localised areas. The DTMs are hydrologically enforced and correctly defines the natural surface drainage and hydrological flow.
